WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:03.580
From previous experiments,

00:00:03.580 --> 00:00:07.580
we've established that our
D-mails are being sent back in time.

00:00:07.580 --> 00:00:11.370
But we couldn't change how
I fared against Faris-tan in our game.

00:00:11.370 --> 00:00:13.910
I'd say that's your problem.

00:00:13.910 --> 00:00:17.500
I guess there is an issue with
accuracy, given Ruka's case too,

00:00:17.500 --> 00:00:19.450
but a few improvements and
we'll have a real time machine--

00:00:19.450 --> 00:00:21.120
Time machine?

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:23.450
You eavesdropped?!

00:00:23.450 --> 00:00:27.250
Faris only brought your order, meow!

00:00:27.250 --> 00:00:29.040
Would you like some
sugar syrup or milk, meow?

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:30.040
No!

00:00:30.040 --> 00:00:32.410
Then I'll give you all of it, Kyouma.

00:00:33.450 --> 00:00:35.250
-Meow, meow!
-There it is!

00:00:35.250 --> 00:00:37.540
Special Technique: Eye Contact Stir!

00:00:37.540 --> 00:00:39.620
-I'm jealous, Okarin! Go die in a fire!
-Kyouma!

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:41.870
-I'm jealous, Okarin! Go die in a fire!
-What's this about a time machine, meow?

00:00:41.870 --> 00:00:46.370
Do you really think such attempts
at seduction will get me to talk?

00:00:46.370 --> 00:00:48.330
I see you're im-purr-vious to it, Kyouma.

00:00:48.330 --> 00:00:50.000
Daru!

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:52.660
-Daru would never betray--
-We made a machine to send e-mails to the past!

00:00:52.660 --> 00:00:55.450
-I did most of the work!
-Have you no shame at all?!

00:00:55.450 --> 00:00:58.290
E-mails to the past...?

00:01:13.330 --> 00:01:18.540
For you, billions and billions of heartbeats

00:01:18.540 --> 00:01:25.200
are nothing at all; just the blink of an eye

00:01:25.200 --> 00:01:30.410
Although I'm trapped by
the past and lament the future

00:01:30.410 --> 00:01:36.330
inevitability won't allow for
even a speck of a miscalculation

00:01:36.330 --> 00:01:42.450
Our dreams and futures that
form and expand into "infinity"

00:01:42.450 --> 00:01:48.330
allow us the right to be vain,

00:01:48.330 --> 00:01:54.540
while the two hands
point out what is "finite"

00:01:54.540 --> 00:01:59.120
All of which leads to a cruel
contract and choice to make

00:01:59.120 --> 00:02:01.370
Hacking to the Gate

00:02:01.370 --> 00:02:08.290
So, now, with each passing
second, I'll cross world lines

00:02:08.290 --> 00:02:13.200
to protect that smile on your face

00:02:13.200 --> 00:02:20.200
Then, once again, into a
time loop without sadness

00:02:20.200 --> 00:02:26.910
I will be swallowed up as a lone observer

00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:35.200
Damn Daru, leaking confidential
information to an outsider...

00:02:35.200 --> 00:02:36.790
Why?

00:02:36.790 --> 00:02:40.250
Why do you see it that way? I just--!

00:02:40.250 --> 00:02:42.330
No! It isn't like that at all!

00:02:42.330 --> 00:02:43.910
I'm...!

00:03:06.660 --> 00:03:08.160
Wh-Wh-What?

00:03:08.160 --> 00:03:09.910
I wasn't crying.

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:12.500
I wasn't crying, just so you know!

00:03:12.500 --> 00:03:14.950
It sure seemed like you were to me...

00:03:14.950 --> 00:03:17.290
Your eyes are still red.

00:03:17.290 --> 00:03:19.000
I-It's not what you think!

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:23.000
-There's just something in my eye...
-Are you out of an old drama or something?

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:24.660
I wasn't crying, okay?!

00:03:24.660 --> 00:03:27.330
So don't pester me about it! Got it?!

00:03:27.330 --> 00:03:30.000
Actually, I haven't said a word about it.

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:32.120
Sh-Shut up!

00:03:51.330 --> 00:03:54.080
-Christina--
-Shut up! Don't talk to me!

00:03:58.700 --> 00:04:02.950
I'll just say this: I cherish you as a friend.

00:04:02.950 --> 00:04:04.950
You can talk to me anytime.

00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:08.040
Okabe...

00:04:09.370 --> 00:04:12.000
Precisely as planned!
She fell right into my trap!

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.250
Yes! Now she's wrapped
around my little finger!

00:04:17.540 --> 00:04:18.830
Hey, now...

00:04:21.500 --> 00:04:23.330
Good work today, meow!

00:04:23.330 --> 00:04:25.040
Oh, Faris-chan!

00:04:25.040 --> 00:04:26.870
Are you going to see Kyouma now?

00:04:26.870 --> 00:04:30.200
Yeah. He asked me to
pick up something for lunch.

00:04:31.370 --> 00:04:35.370
Say, have you seen the
time machine, Mayushii?

00:04:35.370 --> 00:04:36.620
Time...?

00:04:36.620 --> 00:04:39.000
Oh, Phone Microwave-san?

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:40.370
Phone Microwave?

00:04:40.370 --> 00:04:42.620
It makes this lightning
that's all, "Crackle! Zap!"

00:04:42.620 --> 00:04:47.040
It's all tingly and kinda scary...

00:04:47.620 --> 00:04:51.450
Wow! That sounds like a time
machine straight out of the movies!

00:04:51.450 --> 00:04:53.370
Yeah.

00:04:53.370 --> 00:04:58.370
But Mayushii wishes they
wouldn't do stuff with it...

00:04:58.370 --> 00:05:00.580
Why not?

00:05:00.580 --> 00:05:06.250
It feels kind of like Okarin is
getting further and further away...

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.080
This round table
meeting will now come to--

00:05:09.080 --> 00:05:12.040
Okarin, Okarin!

00:05:12.040 --> 00:05:13.950
-What?
-Isn't it strange?

00:05:13.950 --> 00:05:16.580
Mayushii said she isn't cosplaying, but...

00:05:16.580 --> 00:05:19.500
She isn't. That's her school uniform.

00:05:19.500 --> 00:05:21.450
I had school today.

00:05:21.450 --> 00:05:25.290
An ultra-realistic portrayal
of a school uniform...

00:05:25.290 --> 00:05:27.870
You know, talking like that is
usually considered sexual harassment.

00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:29.750
Here's yours, Okarin!

00:05:29.750 --> 00:05:30.660
Thanks.

00:05:30.660 --> 00:05:33.700
Get it right! This is a round table meeting!

00:05:33.700 --> 00:05:36.580
You're the one who asked me
to pick up something for lunch.

00:05:36.580 --> 00:05:38.040
Don't worry about it.

00:05:38.040 --> 00:05:40.080
I doubt he has anything
important to say anyway.

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:43.120
Perhaps you'll change your tune when
you hear today's topic of discussion!

00:05:43.120 --> 00:05:46.120
By which I mean... physical time travel!

00:05:48.080 --> 00:05:51.000
Mayuri. Is there any
barley tea left in the fridge?

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:52.830
Just a sec!

00:05:52.830 --> 00:05:54.870
Ultra-realistic...

00:05:56.080 --> 00:06:00.330
It's me! The Organization has begun
to bring the lab down from the inside!

00:06:00.330 --> 00:06:04.620
My fellow lab members no
longer pay heed to my words!

00:06:04.620 --> 00:06:06.290
It's always been that way.

00:06:06.290 --> 00:06:09.620
Then how can you just brush
aside this great topic of discussion?!

00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:11.580
Because it's obviously impossible.

00:06:11.580 --> 00:06:13.870
We've sent e-mails back in time!

00:06:13.870 --> 00:06:15.870
-Who says we can't--
-We can't.

00:06:15.870 --> 00:06:18.660
We can only send a little over 36 bytes.

00:06:18.660 --> 00:06:22.450
Three messages six Japanese
characters-long. Any more is impossible.

00:06:22.450 --> 00:06:26.370
But if you'd like to try, why
not experiment on yourself?

00:06:27.080 --> 00:06:29.580
If you don't mind turning
into a Gel-Okarin, of course.

00:06:29.580 --> 00:06:31.330
Oh, a Gel-Okarin?

00:06:31.330 --> 00:06:33.080
Ooh, burn!

00:06:33.080 --> 00:06:38.080
SERN's experiments have proven
the difficulty of physical time travel.

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:42.580
If the LHC, the world's largest
particle collider couldn't do it,

00:06:42.580 --> 00:06:44.500
there's no way this equipment can.

00:06:44.500 --> 00:06:47.040
Then how were we
able to send the e-mails?!

00:06:47.040 --> 00:06:49.870
I don't know. That's the real question.

00:06:49.870 --> 00:06:53.500
As we discussed before, SERN
is attempting to achieve time travel

00:06:53.500 --> 00:06:56.160
through the use of a black hole and a lifter.

00:06:56.160 --> 00:06:59.660
This Phone Microwave most
likely works in the same way.

00:06:59.660 --> 00:07:03.870
Yet, whatever functions as
our lifter isn't in the microwave.

00:07:03.870 --> 00:07:04.870
Where is it, then?

00:07:04.870 --> 00:07:06.450
I don't know.

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:09.660
Plus we're only able to send
D-mails at certain times of the day.

00:07:09.660 --> 00:07:14.620
For a machine that sends e-mails
back in time, it's still very shoddy.

00:07:14.620 --> 00:07:18.540
We need to solve these mysteries
before we move any further ahead.

00:07:18.540 --> 00:07:19.910
That's no fun!

00:07:19.910 --> 00:07:24.200
99% of science is unexciting humdrum.

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:26.330
If you profess to be a scientist, then--

00:07:26.330 --> 00:07:29.910
I told you, I am not a scientist!
I'm a "mad scientist"!

00:07:29.910 --> 00:07:33.790
This guy's hopeless. Better do
something about him quick...

00:07:33.790 --> 00:07:35.540
Miss Makise?

00:07:35.540 --> 00:07:37.500
Don't tell me you're quoting...

00:07:37.500 --> 00:07:41.750
Shut up! Don't say
any more! It's not like that!

00:07:41.750 --> 00:07:43.620
Just get to the point!

00:07:43.620 --> 00:07:46.160
All right, then. Status updates.

00:07:46.160 --> 00:07:51.370
How is the translation of the data on
SERN's server coming along, Christina?

00:07:51.370 --> 00:07:54.950
-Or shall I say... @channeler!
-I told you, it's not like that!

00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:58.370
-Yet your ID is bright red.
-Is not!

00:08:01.250 --> 00:08:03.540
Th-There's nothing of note to report.

00:08:03.540 --> 00:08:06.540
I see. Continue to investigate...

00:08:06.540 --> 00:08:08.080
-...@channeler!
-Don't call me that!

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:10.620
You're next, Daru.
How's the hacking coming along?

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:11.540
No change.

00:08:11.540 --> 00:08:14.660
Pretty much at a
standstill until we can analyze

00:08:14.660 --> 00:08:16.660
the mystery program on the other server.

00:08:16.660 --> 00:08:18.660
Can't the IBN 5100 handle that?

00:08:18.660 --> 00:08:21.830
Easier said than done, dude.

00:08:21.830 --> 00:08:23.290
What do you mean?

00:08:23.290 --> 00:08:24.540
What do you mean?

00:08:24.540 --> 00:08:26.950
You haven't deciphered it yet?

00:08:26.950 --> 00:08:29.410
Huh? How would I do that?

00:08:30.910 --> 00:08:34.700
-The IBN 5100! Where is it?!
-How should I know?!

00:08:37.000 --> 00:08:38.790
It can't be...!

00:08:43.120 --> 00:08:45.500
What's gotten into you, Okarin?

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:47.700
Christina...

00:08:47.700 --> 00:08:53.080
Have I not found the IBN 5100...?

00:08:53.080 --> 00:08:57.370
Huh? We don't even know
where to find one in the first place.

00:09:01.540 --> 00:09:02.910
I see.

00:09:02.910 --> 00:09:08.040
So, I'm to believe you
actually found an IBN 5100?

00:09:08.040 --> 00:09:11.620
Yes. The two of us carried it here.

00:09:11.620 --> 00:09:15.580
But you're the only
one with any memory of it.

00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:19.580
The D-mails must've greatly altered the past.

00:09:19.580 --> 00:09:21.200
Greatly?

00:09:21.200 --> 00:09:25.790
But we've only sent simple messages!

00:09:25.790 --> 00:09:28.330
It's the "Butterfly Effect."

00:09:28.330 --> 00:09:31.330
Sending a message back in
time causes the world line to split.

00:09:31.330 --> 00:09:36.660
From a world where we didn't buy a
Loto 6 ticket to one where we did, for example.

00:09:36.660 --> 00:09:41.750
As a result, events and facts that
happened before change ever so slightly.

00:09:41.750 --> 00:09:45.370
Like billiards, a single change
can trigger further changes,

00:09:45.370 --> 00:09:48.370
resulting in even greater changes.

00:09:48.370 --> 00:09:52.290
It's one of the most famous
risks of altering the past.

00:09:52.290 --> 00:09:55.410
Then where is the IBN 5100?

00:09:55.410 --> 00:09:59.290
Let me turn the tables: Where did you find it?

00:09:59.290 --> 00:10:00.370
Yes.

00:10:00.370 --> 00:10:06.620
Yes, my father said it was stored at the shrine,

00:10:06.620 --> 00:10:09.330
but now it's nowhere to be found...

00:10:09.330 --> 00:10:10.950
Oh...

00:10:11.830 --> 00:10:13.700
Well?

00:10:13.700 --> 00:10:18.790
There was an IBN 5100
at the Yanabayashi Shrine...

00:10:18.790 --> 00:10:21.410
...but not anymore.

00:10:21.410 --> 00:10:24.040
They're not sure who took it, or even when.

00:10:24.040 --> 00:10:26.200
A dead-end...

00:10:26.200 --> 00:10:30.290
Storing a computer at a
shrine sure sounds strange!

00:10:30.290 --> 00:10:32.830
I wonder who did it...

00:10:40.290 --> 00:10:42.870
-Faris-chan!
-Meow?

00:10:42.870 --> 00:10:47.450
Here are the ten questions I came up
with for the maids at the next event...

00:10:47.450 --> 00:10:49.830
Let's see here!

00:10:49.830 --> 00:10:54.580
"If you could go back in time and
redo one thing, what would it be?"

00:10:54.580 --> 00:10:57.160
What would you do, Faris-chan?

00:10:58.620 --> 00:11:01.540
Good question! Faris...

00:11:01.540 --> 00:11:03.410
...doesn't focus on the past!

00:11:03.410 --> 00:11:06.580
As cat-girl maids who
bring happiness to everyone,

00:11:06.580 --> 00:11:09.450
it's our duty to always move forward!

00:11:11.080 --> 00:11:13.410
Oh! Phone, phone!

00:11:13.410 --> 00:11:15.540
Hi! This is Faris, meow!

00:11:15.540 --> 00:11:16.540
Kyouma?

00:11:16.540 --> 00:11:18.700
Meow? A computer?

00:11:18.700 --> 00:11:20.620
An IBN 5100.

00:11:20.620 --> 00:11:23.700
Is it true that you stored
one at the Yanabayashi Shrine?

00:11:23.700 --> 00:11:27.120
I don't really remember,

00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:31.290
but Daddy did have lots
of old computers, meow.

00:11:33.870 --> 00:11:36.330
Kyouma...

00:11:36.330 --> 00:11:41.080
Does this have something to do
with this time machine of yours?

00:11:44.700 --> 00:11:46.410
Wow, look!

00:11:46.410 --> 00:11:49.370
An Oopa! A Metal Oopa!

00:11:50.830 --> 00:11:53.200
Oh, you still want a Metal Oopa?

00:11:53.200 --> 00:11:54.830
"Still"?

00:11:59.290 --> 00:12:01.370
How long are we gonna
stand here? Let's get going.

00:12:01.370 --> 00:12:02.830
Oh, wait!

00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:04.450
Daru-kun!

00:12:04.450 --> 00:12:06.830
Sorry for the wait!

00:12:10.200 --> 00:12:11.370
What are you shopping for?!

00:12:11.370 --> 00:12:14.660
Couldn't help it! I spotted
some limited edition swag!

00:12:14.660 --> 00:12:16.290
As you'd say,

00:12:16.290 --> 00:12:19.660
"This fateful encounter was
truly the choice of Steins Gate!"

00:12:19.660 --> 00:12:21.330
Don't use that term lightly!

00:12:21.330 --> 00:12:24.250
Why are you two tagging along anyway?!

00:12:24.250 --> 00:12:26.790
You should just hold down
the fort with my assistant.

00:12:26.790 --> 00:12:30.870
STFU! I can't turn down an
opportunity to visit Faris-tan at home!

00:12:30.870 --> 00:12:33.830
Mayushii wants to visit her too!

00:12:33.830 --> 00:12:36.330
Why the heck did she invite me over anyway?

00:12:36.330 --> 00:12:38.330
Oh, it's Kirari-chan!

00:12:38.330 --> 00:12:40.450
Hey! Mayuri!

00:12:40.450 --> 00:12:42.250
Sheesh...

00:12:42.250 --> 00:12:44.750
The IBN 5100...

00:12:53.620 --> 00:12:55.330
Shining Finger!

00:12:58.700 --> 00:13:00.330
Hey! Wait!

00:13:04.290 --> 00:13:05.370
Shining--!

00:13:05.370 --> 00:13:08.200
Moeka! Kiryu Moeka!

00:13:25.290 --> 00:13:27.660
Why...?

00:13:27.660 --> 00:13:31.750
FB said it would be there...

00:13:33.540 --> 00:13:35.200
Okabe-kun...?

00:13:35.200 --> 00:13:38.580
You mentioned the IBN 5100 just now--

00:13:38.580 --> 00:13:41.910
Do you know where it is?!

00:13:44.160 --> 00:13:47.200
You don't know either?

00:13:47.200 --> 00:13:49.830
You don't know...?

00:13:57.080 --> 00:13:58.950
Okarin!

00:13:58.950 --> 00:14:01.040
Oh, Moeka-san?

00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:02.000
Yeah...

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.410
Okarin!

00:14:03.410 --> 00:14:06.750
Moeka-san is so pretty and stylish!

00:14:06.750 --> 00:14:09.580
I bet she'd look amazing if she cosplayed!

00:14:09.580 --> 00:14:12.080
Yeah...

00:14:12.080 --> 00:14:16.250
Hold on, Mayuri.
You know who Shining Finger is?

00:14:16.250 --> 00:14:18.410
Huh? Yeah.

00:14:18.410 --> 00:14:20.250
How?! How is that possible?!

00:14:20.250 --> 00:14:25.120
You brought her to the lab...!

00:14:25.120 --> 00:14:27.660
After Moeka sent her D-mail,

00:14:27.660 --> 00:14:31.370
her existence was
erased from their memories.

00:14:31.370 --> 00:14:34.580
And now, after Ruka's D-mail,

00:14:34.580 --> 00:14:37.450
everyone knows who Moeka is again...

00:14:38.700 --> 00:14:43.910
Each time a D-mail alters the past,
things start to change little by little?

00:14:58.910 --> 00:15:00.750
You're sure this is the place?

00:15:00.750 --> 00:15:02.540
I'm sure!

00:15:02.540 --> 00:15:06.160
Let's see... It looks
like she's on the top floor.

00:15:13.200 --> 00:15:16.200
The young mistress will be here shortly.

00:15:16.200 --> 00:15:18.160
Please wait here.

00:15:22.290 --> 00:15:25.540
Butler cafes aren't really my thing, you know...

00:15:25.540 --> 00:15:29.540
A real-life butler! I've never seen one before!

00:15:31.830 --> 00:15:34.000
Look! The people are like garbage!

00:15:34.000 --> 00:15:36.500
What a magnificent view!

00:15:36.500 --> 00:15:37.750
Okarin...

00:15:37.750 --> 00:15:39.450
I knew he'd say that.

00:15:39.450 --> 00:15:40.870
Sorry for the wait, meow!

00:15:40.870 --> 00:15:43.540
Oh, Faris-chan!

00:15:43.540 --> 00:15:46.120
Now I get to witness Faris-tan in plain clothes!

00:15:46.120 --> 00:15:48.620
What good fortune!

00:15:50.410 --> 00:15:52.080
-Faris Meow-Meow!
-Meow?

00:15:52.080 --> 00:15:56.450
It would seem prudent to
ask who you really are now.

00:15:56.450 --> 00:15:58.580
Faris is...

00:15:59.500 --> 00:16:00.790
...Faris, meow!

00:16:00.790 --> 00:16:02.450
Don't toy with me!

00:16:02.450 --> 00:16:05.000
If you won't explain, then I'm leaving!

00:16:05.000 --> 00:16:07.500
Fine, meow...

00:16:08.830 --> 00:16:11.660
Faris' family originally owned...

00:16:11.660 --> 00:16:13.660
...all the land around here!

00:16:13.660 --> 00:16:16.330
Wait, does that mean Akiba is...?

00:16:16.330 --> 00:16:17.790
Yep! That's right!

00:16:17.790 --> 00:16:19.790
Huh? What about Akiba now?

00:16:19.790 --> 00:16:23.700
It's part of her real name: Akiha Rumiho-chan!

00:16:23.700 --> 00:16:25.580
La-la-la-la! I can't hear you!

00:16:25.580 --> 00:16:28.120
Faris-tan's real name is Faris-tan!

00:16:28.120 --> 00:16:30.620
An embarrassing attempt at escaping reality...

00:16:30.620 --> 00:16:33.040
Incidentally, Faris was the one who asked

00:16:33.040 --> 00:16:36.000
for moe culture to be
introduced into Akiba, meow!

00:16:36.000 --> 00:16:37.250
Wha...?! You're that influential?!

00:16:37.250 --> 00:16:39.620
And, being the angel
you are, you use May Queen

00:16:39.620 --> 00:16:42.500
to personally spread moe
culture throughout the land!

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:43.910
She's so l33t!

00:16:43.910 --> 00:16:47.620
And I have l33t eyes for
recognizing someone so l33t!

00:16:47.620 --> 00:16:52.120
But please don't tell
anyone else about this, meow.

00:16:52.120 --> 00:16:55.500
I want everyone to treat me with
the same "Faris love" as always!

00:16:55.500 --> 00:16:57.540
I will! With every ounce of my being!

00:16:57.540 --> 00:16:58.910
Thanks, meow, meow!

00:16:58.910 --> 00:17:02.700
Never mind the meows!
We're here about the IBN 5100!

00:17:02.700 --> 00:17:05.120
Oh, that, meow?

00:17:05.120 --> 00:17:09.790
But before that, I have a small request...

00:17:09.790 --> 00:17:12.000
Are you trying to extort us?!

00:17:12.000 --> 00:17:14.040
I promise, it's nothing much!

00:17:14.040 --> 00:17:18.080
I just want to use the
D-mail one time, that's all!

00:17:18.080 --> 00:17:20.910
But of course! You can
send as many as you'd like!

00:17:20.910 --> 00:17:24.160
Hold on! No one outside the
lab is allowed to know about--

00:17:24.160 --> 00:17:27.950
Then can't we just make
Faris-chan a lab member too?

00:17:27.950 --> 00:17:30.080
No, wait! Hold on!

00:17:30.080 --> 00:17:32.540
It's too dangerous to send any more--

00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:36.580
So you get to send messages about
the Loto 6 for your own personal greed,

00:17:36.580 --> 00:17:38.250
but Faris-tan doesn't?!

00:17:38.250 --> 00:17:39.580
It's just one time!

00:17:39.580 --> 00:17:42.250
No, that's not what it's about...

00:17:42.250 --> 00:17:49.080
Still, there's no guarantee
we'll find the IBN 5100 on our own.

00:17:49.080 --> 00:17:54.200
If she can help us track it down...

00:17:54.200 --> 00:17:55.080
All right.

00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:59.160
But you will have to become a
lab member, just as Mayuri said.

00:17:59.160 --> 00:18:02.830
As of today, you are
Lab Member 007: Akiha Rumi--

00:18:02.830 --> 00:18:05.620
La-la-la-la! I-I can't hear you!

00:18:07.950 --> 00:18:10.120
Done!

00:18:10.120 --> 00:18:12.950
You're sure you want
this sent ten years back?

00:18:12.950 --> 00:18:14.750
I'm sure, meow!

00:18:14.750 --> 00:18:16.870
What's it say?

00:18:16.870 --> 00:18:19.040
It's... a secret, meow.

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:21.120
That won't do!

00:18:21.120 --> 00:18:24.660
As the head of the lab,
I need to know this sort of--!

00:18:24.660 --> 00:18:25.580
Too bad.

00:18:25.580 --> 00:18:28.910
Boys aren't allowed to
meddle in girls' private lives!

00:18:28.910 --> 00:18:31.620
I think it's wrong to
read other people's e-mail.

00:18:31.620 --> 00:18:33.660
I totally agree!

00:18:35.370 --> 00:18:37.330
Oh, all right...

00:18:37.330 --> 00:18:40.500
Okay, wait with your
finger on the send button.

00:18:45.080 --> 00:18:46.080
Hello?

00:18:46.080 --> 00:18:49.910
It's me. Give me a status report--

00:18:51.160 --> 00:18:53.580
-She hung up on me!
-I don't blame her.

00:18:53.580 --> 00:18:57.290
Lousy Christina!
You're supposed to be my assistant!

00:18:57.290 --> 00:18:58.120
Hello?

00:18:58.120 --> 00:19:00.790
It's Hououin Kyouma. Don't hang up on me.

00:19:00.790 --> 00:19:02.160
Hououin?

00:19:02.160 --> 00:19:05.370
Oh, it's you, Okabe.
I thought it was a prank caller.

00:19:05.370 --> 00:19:08.080
You clearly saw it was me calling.

00:19:08.080 --> 00:19:12.040
Still, you were so creepy-sounding
that I couldn't help it.

00:19:13.120 --> 00:19:17.700
In other words, you fear the great Hououin--

00:19:19.450 --> 00:19:21.500
She did it again! She hung up again!

00:19:21.500 --> 00:19:23.000
What's taking so long, Okarin?

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:23.870
Hold on!

00:19:23.870 --> 00:19:26.870
Curse that cold-hearted,
prodigal, perverted genius girl!

00:19:28.330 --> 00:19:30.750
-Hello?
-Now you listen here, The Zomb--!

00:19:35.790 --> 00:19:36.790
Hello?

00:19:36.790 --> 00:19:39.660
My name is Okabe Rintaro...

00:19:39.660 --> 00:19:40.910
How can I help you?

00:19:40.910 --> 00:19:46.200
I humbly asketh you to activate the
Phone Microwave (Temporary Name)

00:19:46.200 --> 00:19:50.120
as per the settings
provided in my prior e-mail.

00:19:50.120 --> 00:19:52.700
You should've said so at the start.

00:19:52.700 --> 00:19:57.080
You used "asketh" wrong, by the way.
You're an embarrassment to yourself.

00:19:57.080 --> 00:19:59.910
Also, it's about time you
drop the "Temporary Name"--

00:19:59.910 --> 00:20:02.450
Sh-Shut yer hole, Celeb 17!

00:20:02.450 --> 00:20:04.450
Think you're so great even though you suck--

00:20:04.450 --> 00:20:06.080
-Oh, nothing.
-Are they not on good terms?

00:20:06.080 --> 00:20:08.250
-No, I humbly ask...
-Actually, I think it's the opposite.

00:20:08.250 --> 00:20:11.330
-...that you remain on the line.
-I agree with Mayushii.

00:20:12.660 --> 00:20:14.660
"Send?"
Maybe I...

00:20:15.750 --> 00:20:18.750
Maybe I don't need to after all...

00:20:18.750 --> 00:20:20.870
Faris.

00:20:20.870 --> 00:20:22.200
The discharge has begun.

00:20:22.200 --> 00:20:23.750
Send it!

00:20:44.620 --> 00:20:46.660
Umm...

00:20:46.660 --> 00:20:47.620
Who are you?

00:20:47.620 --> 00:20:49.250
Huh?

00:20:50.120 --> 00:20:51.910
Daddy!

00:20:53.700 --> 00:20:55.660
"Daddy"?

00:20:55.660 --> 00:20:57.500
Were you talking with Kyouma, meow?

00:20:57.500 --> 00:20:58.870
Yes.

00:20:58.870 --> 00:21:03.370
Well, I must be going.
Please, make yourselves at home.

00:21:06.830 --> 00:21:10.250
Your father sure seems dignified, Faris-chan!

00:21:10.250 --> 00:21:14.750
He's Faris-tan's progenitor, all right!

00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:16.660
Umm...!

00:21:16.660 --> 00:21:19.700
Are you familiar with the IBN 5100?

00:21:20.370 --> 00:21:22.660
That name certainly takes me back.

00:21:22.660 --> 00:21:24.000
We're looking for one!

00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:28.620
I gave mine away long ago, I'm sorry to say.

00:21:28.620 --> 00:21:31.870
Did you happen to give it
to the Yanabayashi Shrine?

00:21:31.870 --> 00:21:35.620
A shrine? No, I'm afraid not.

00:21:35.620 --> 00:21:37.370
Well, I must be going.

00:21:46.450 --> 00:21:49.290
Before Faris sent her D-mail,

00:21:49.290 --> 00:21:53.910
the IBN 5100 disappeared
after being stored at the shrine.

00:21:53.910 --> 00:21:58.870
But now it was never
stored there to begin with.

00:21:58.870 --> 00:22:03.620
With each message,
things change more and more.

00:22:03.620 --> 00:22:08.620
There could be things changing
out there I don't even know about.

00:22:16.330 --> 00:22:21.500
It's possible we've done things
now that can never be undone...

00:22:21.500 --> 00:22:23.450
Okarin! Okarin!

00:22:23.450 --> 00:22:28.450
Mayushii's going to buy an Ai Sword
doujinshi in Nakano before going home.

00:22:28.450 --> 00:22:31.330
Ai Sword? Oh, by Kouga Yui?

00:22:31.330 --> 00:22:34.330
Nakano's a pretty long way to go.

00:22:34.330 --> 00:22:35.580
Yeah.

00:22:35.580 --> 00:22:39.450
I wish they'd open a
Toranoana shop here too.

00:22:39.450 --> 00:22:41.330
What are you talking about?

00:22:41.330 --> 00:22:43.620
There's one right--

00:22:43.620 --> 00:22:44.750
Huh?!

00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:49.370
Don't be silly, Okarin.

00:22:49.370 --> 00:22:51.700
You know there isn't one in Akiba.

00:22:54.910 --> 00:22:59.160
Trapped by the covenant

00:22:59.160 --> 00:23:03.540
and shown the outline of false evidence

00:23:03.540 --> 00:23:07.660
the heaven and earth

00:23:07.660 --> 00:23:12.660
of life lets time blindly flow by

00:23:12.660 --> 00:23:18.040
Flutter, butterfly, oh, miraculous butterfly!

00:23:18.040 --> 00:23:21.540
I give myself to you

00:23:21.540 --> 00:23:25.870
Oh, butterfly of tears, dazzling butterfly!

00:23:25.870 --> 00:23:28.700
It's all...

00:23:28.700 --> 00:23:33.620
...about to be rewritten now

00:23:53.660 --> 00:23:55.410
"I'm watching you"

